    Defines intersection types that can be applied to data sets. The intersection requires a predicate to compare elements in each data set, usually defining an attribute of elements in data set A that may or may not match an attribute of elements in data set B. Simple predicates often compare a single attribute (such as a single-field key), and more complex predicates often compare unique combinations of multiple attributes.
